import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['age'].plot.hist(bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the victims?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

    plt.ylabel('Number of Victims')

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    incident_counts = data['type'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(incident_counts, labels=incident_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of incident types that resulted in the victims' deaths?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
